
// This Hyperlambda code connects to a SQLite database using the Northwind database configuration and constructs a SQL query to count distinct values in a specified column from the "Customers" table. It dynamically creates a distinct count function using [strings.concat] and removes the [distinct_column] argument. It then adds any additional conditions from the arguments to the [where] clause, executes the query, and returns the results. The code uses slots like [data.connect], [strings.concat], [remove-nodes], [add], [data.read], and [return-nodes] to achieve this functionality.
data.connect:[generic|northwind]
   database-type:sqlite
   set-name:x:./*/data.read/*/columns/*/distinct_functor
      strings.concat
         .:"count(distinct "
         get-value:x:@.arguments/*/distinct_column
         .:)
   remove-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/distinct_column
   add:x:./*/data.read/*/where/*
      get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
   data.read
      database-type:sqlite
      table:Customers
      columns
         distinct_functor
            as:count
      where
         and
   return-nodes:x:@data.read/*/*
